 The Glory steals the thunder 
 STAR RACER				 										Calcutta: Steal The Glory passed the crucial test before going into the Classics, winning the 1,400m Octogonal Cup handsomely on Sunday. The hot-favourite colt from trainer Daniel Davids yard not only conceded 6kg handicap to his potential rival, Afforce, but he also handed the Vijay Singh-trainee a seven-length-plus beating. Moreover, his impressive timing of 1.27.19 seconds, on the winter race track, had left the rival quarters amazed. He has vast scope for improvement, said someone close to the stable. However, jockey Imran Chisty, who partnered the 6-10 favourite to victory, only smiled when asked if Glory was going to be his winner in the Guineas on December 8.				 										The afternoons other hero was jockey C. Alford. The champion jockey notched up a treble through Robin Corners Guineas hope Monticello, and a brace of winners  Megillah and Sephora  for trainer Harvinder Bath.				 										RESULTS				 										1. Senor Pele Handicap 1,600m: (3-6-5-1) Monticello (C.Alford) 1; Desire Prince (Gajender) 2; Elegant Road (Chisty) 3; Sportsman (Amil) 4. Won by: 4-1/2, 1, 6-3/4; (1-45.27). Tote: Win Rs 15; Place: 11, 31; Quinella: 47; Shp: 56; Tanala: 92. Fav: Monticello (3). Winner trained by Corner.				 										2. Siranoosh Handicap 1,100m: (1-2-6-7) Thousand Stars (Brij) 1; Way To The Stars (Mark) 2; Arrayal (Afzal) 3; Regal Venture (Chisty) 4. Won by: 6-3/4, 1-1/2, Lnk; (1-8.48). Tote: Win Rs 373; Place: 71, 17, 16; Quinella: 771; Shp: 48; Tanala: 4,481. Fav: Helegonia (5). Winner trained by R.Alford.				 										3. Crystal Man Handicap 1,200m: (5-7-4-3) Royal Ballerina (Islam) 1; Vancouver (Afzal) 2; Matrix (Domingo) 3; Stride To Strike (Mark) 4. Won by: 4-3/4, 3-1/4, 1-1/2; (1-17.59). Tote: Win Rs 16; Place: 12, 19, 19; Quinella: 60; Shp: 57; Tanala: 284. Fav: Royal Ballerina (5). Winner trained by Javed.				 										4. Myall King Handicap 1,400m: (5-1-4-6) Megillah (C.Alford) 1; Triple Edge (Chisty) 2; Sweet Success (Som) 3; 